Program: Discovery
Title: Infrared and microwaves in space
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz6f
Last Broadcast Date: 13 June 2006
A look at the uses of infrared and microwave astronomy. The programme is presented by former NASA astronaut and MIT professor of astronomy Jeffrey Hoffman. He looks at the other end of the light spectrum, and how certain light can only be seen from space.